          "reviewBody": "We applied for admission for my daughter in 4th grade. They conducted an interview test. We thought it was a general basic question, but they asked all 5 subjects, so my daughter couldn't clear\n\nWe applied here for Qur'an learning purposes, so we requested that they know that my daughter has been studying Velammal CBSE. Their syllabus is different, and we showed her mark sheet to them. She cleared all subjects, but they never cared about it.\n\nWe got frustrated for the reasons below\n\nThis Muslim school never helped Muslim\n\nMr. Anjum told you your daughter is average, so it affected other students in this school. How dared he? I was fasting, so I controlled myself and left.\n\nMy daughter is 8 years old we applied for 4th grade, not for MBBS seat. Why did they behave like that? they are shameful.",
